data.title: Meet Cleveland Cavaliers shooting guard Kyle Korver

data.text:
New Cavaliers shooting guard Kyle Korver made his debut with Cleveland against the Utah Jazz on Jan. 10.

The Cavs sent guard Mo Williams, guard/forward Mike Dunleavy plus cash considerations and a protected first-round draft pick (first possible pick is the Cavaliers’ 2019 first round pick) to the Hawks for Korver, who in 32 games (21 starts) for Atlanta this season averaged 9.5 points, 2.8 rebounds and 2.3 assists in 27.9 minutes per game.

In his first game with the Wine & Gold, Korver scored two points and grabbed three rebounds in 17 minutes.
